The paper deals with the optimization of scheduling in wireless systems, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new algebraic framework for optimization, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper uses numerical simulations to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
